PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1774530671
OL,3,COrthopaedic surgeon who broke ankle on
OL,4,Ccoastal walk rescued by coastguard
OL,6,FHis friends called 999 and asked for
OL,7,Fthe coastguard, leading St Austell
OL,8,FCoastguard Rescue Team to respond.
OL,10,FOfficer in charge Martin Cocks said:
OL,11,F"Chris had exactly the right footwear
OL,12,Fand was well-equipped, but handling
OL,13,Fdogs under slippery conditions can
OL,14,Flead to accidents.
OL,16,F"Unfortunately, given the thick mud
OL,17,Fand weather we've had, coastal paths
OL,18,Fcan quickly become dangerous."
OL,26,@sD@AOUzD@^O]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
